<title>USA: RESEARCH ALERT - Gucci cut.</title>
<headline>RESEARCH ALERT - Gucci cut.</headline>
<text>
<p>-- Robertson Stephens said Thursday it had cut its rating for luxury goods maker Gucci Group to long-term attractive from buy.</p>
<p>-- A spokeswoman for the firm said the downgrade was based on the recent devaluation of the Japanese yen against the dollar.</p>
<p>-- Traders said the cut prompted a drop in the company's American Depositary Receipts. The ADRs were down 4-5/8 to 62-1/4.</p>
<p>-- Volume was 1.2 million ADRs, more than three times normal daily trade.</p>
<p>((--Ian Simpson, Wall Street desk, (212) 859-1879))</p>
